## File Structure

```
├── Data/                        # Input and output datasets
├── Cache/                       # Cached embeddings, entities, event summaries
├── Dashboard/Outputfiles/       # Generated charts (radar plots, cluster scatter)
├── scrape.py                    # Article content scraper
├── ollama_annotate.py           # PEST annotation runner
├── ollama_client.py             # LLM annotation logic and prompts
├── article_to_event_level.py    # Full clustering pipeline
├── regressor_jesse.py           # SVR regression model for PEST prediction
├── streamlit_app.py             # Dashboard
└── dataset.py                   # Data loading utilities
```

---

## Notes

- Ollama must be running locally before executing any annotation or description generation steps.
- The `llama3.2:1b` model is used for both annotation and event description generation. Larger models will improve quality but increase runtime.
- Articles flagged as `relevant: false` by the annotation step are excluded from clustering.
- The `regressor_jesse.py` file trains an SVR model to predict PEST scores from embeddings, useful for applying scores to unannotated datasets.